.TH SIM_TORCH "9" "2026-06-05" "LinuxCNC Documentation" "HAL Component"
.SH NAME

sim_torch \- Simulated plasma torch arc voltage
.SH SYNOPSIS
.HP
.B load sim_torch [sim_torch.\fIN\fB]
.SH DESCRIPTION


Simulates a plasma torch arc voltage signal for testing.
Generates ramp-up, overshoot, and steady-state voltage with
configurable noise. No hardware interaction.

Originally a Python userspace component (bin/sim-torch).

.SH FUNCTIONS
.TP
\fBsim_torch.\fIN\fB\fR (requires a floating-point thread)
.SH PINS
.TP
.B sim_torch.\fIN\fB.cut-noise\fR float in \fR(default: \fI0.75\fR) \fR
noise amplitude during cut (volts)
.TP
.B sim_torch.\fIN\fB.cycles\fR s32 in \fR(default: \fI200\fR) \fR
overshoot duration (servo cycles)
.TP
.B sim_torch.\fIN\fB.on-delay\fR s32 in \fR(default: \fI10\fR) \fR
delay from start until overshoot begins (cycles)
.TP
.B sim_torch.\fIN\fB.offset\fR float in \fR(default: \fI0.0\fR) \fR
cut voltage offset (-10..10 volts)
.TP
.B sim_torch.\fIN\fB.overshoot\fR s32 in \fR(default: \fI50\fR) \fR
overshoot percentage of cut voltage (0..100)
.TP
.B sim_torch.\fIN\fB.ramp-noise\fR float in \fR(default: \fI5.0\fR) \fR
